@* Overview page: links into one-feature-per-page demos. *@
<section class="panel">
    <h2>HyperRazor HTMX Demo</h2>
    <p>Choose a feature demo. Each page is focused on one HTMX + SSR behavior.</p>
    <p class="demo-caption">
        Tip: keep the inspector panel visible while navigating to see request and response headers evolve.
    </p>
    <div class="demo-note" role="note">
        <strong>How To Use This Demo:</strong> start on any page, perform one action, then compare
        the visual change with inspector header data to connect behavior to transport-level HX details.
        Navigation links are <code>hx-boost</code>-enabled and swap only the main layout region.
    </div>
    <p class="demo-caption">
        The <code>Overview</code> and <code>Server Trigger</code> nav items now use the Minimal API routes
        <code>/minimal</code> and <code>/minimal/basic</code>. The remaining pages still use MVC endpoints.
    </p>
</section>
